    "Dirac Matrix Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "DiracMatrix", 
    "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "GammaMatrices[n] returns the n Euclidean gamma matrices of dimension 2 \
\\[LeftFloor] n/2 \\[RightFloor] (equivalent to EuclideanGammaMatrices[n]). \
GammaMatrices[\\[Eta]] returns gamma matrices satisfying the Clifford \
relation { \\[Gamma]^\\[Mu], \\[Gamma]^\\[Nu] } = 2 \\[Eta] \\[Mu] \\[Nu] I \
for any real symmetric metric \\[Eta]; for a flat signed-diagonal metric the \
result is i \\[ThinSpace] \\[CapitalGamma]^\\[Mu] on time-like indices and \
\\[CapitalGamma]^\\[Mu] on space-like indices; for a general metric a \
vielbein decomposition is used.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "GammaMatrices", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> 
    "", "windowtitle" -> "GammaMatrices", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
